# CODEOWNERS — review requirements for sensitive paths
#
# GitHub docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Format: <pattern>  <@user-or-team>
# Replace @your-github-username with the actual GitHub username(s).
#
# To enforce: enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection settings.
# See docs/admin/github-branch-protection.md

# Default: all files require at least one review
*                          @your-github-username

# Auth + key management (highest security sensitivity)
admin_auth.py              @your-github-username
key_store.py               @your-github-username

# Agent execution (filesystem write surface)
agent/tools.py             @your-github-username
agent/loop.py              @your-github-username

# Core proxy (request routing, rate limiting, CORS)
proxy.py                   @your-github-username

# Model routing
router/                    @your-github-username

# CI/CD and repo configuration
.github/                   @your-github-username
.claude/                   @your-github-username
Makefile                   @your-github-username

# Documentation
docs/                      @your-github-username
CLAUDE.md                  @your-github-username
